get template "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
============================================================

NAME
----

get template - Retrieves the directory name of the current

SYNOPSIS
--------

Retrieves the directory name of the current
[theme](/Glossary#Theme "Glossary"), without the trailing slash.

In the case a child theme is being used, the directory name of the
parent theme will be returned. Use
[`get_stylesheet()`](/Function_Reference/get_stylesheet "Function Reference/get stylesheet")
to get the directory name of the child theme.

USAGE
-----

` <?php get_template() ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

This tag has no parameters.

RETURN VALUES
-------------

 `` `(string)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   Directory name of the current theme (without the trailing slash).

EXAMPLES
--------

NOTES
-----

-   Uses:
    [`get_option()`](/Function_Reference/get_option "Function Reference/get option")
    to retrieve the
    [template](/Option_Reference#Themes "Option Reference") option.
-   Uses:
    [`apply_filters()`](/Function_Reference/apply_filters "Function Reference/apply filters")
    to apply the
    [template](/Plugin_API/Filter_Reference/template "Plugin API/Filter Reference/template")
    filters on the retrieved *template* option.

CHANGE LOG
----------

Since: 1.5.0

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`get_template()` is located in `wp-includes/theme.php`.

